# Question 1------------------

gcd <- function(a, b) {
  # returns the greatest common divisor for a and b
  # Args:
  # a: positive integer
  # b: positive integer
  # Return:
  # positive integer, the greatest common divisor in one dimension
  if (as.integer(a) != a || as.integer(b) != b || a < 1 || b < 1) {
    stop("a and b must be positive integers.")
  }

  while (a != b && b != 0) {
    if (a > b) {
      division_result <- a %/% b

      remainder <- a %% b

      a <- b

      b <- remainder
    }

    else {
      division_result <- b %/% a

      remainder <- b %% a

      b <- remainder
    }
  }

  a
}



gcd_three <- function(a, b, c) {
  # returns the greatest common divisor for a, b and c
  # Args:
  # a: positive integer
  # b: positive integer
  # c: positive integer
  # Return:
  # positive integer, the greatest common divisor in one dimension
  if (as.integer(a) != a || as.integer(b) != b || as.integer(c) != c || a < 1 || b < 1 || c < 1) {
    stop("a, b and c must be positive integers.")
  }
  gcd_ab <- gcd(a, b)
  gcd(gcd_ab, c)
}


# Question 2-------------------------------

#' Returns true if x is a prime number, false otherwise
#'

is_prime <- function(x) {
  # returns whether a positive integer is prime
  # Args:
  # x: positive integer
  # Return:
  # a boolean, whether the statement is true
  if (as.integer(x) != x || x <= 0) {
    stop("x must be a positive integer.")
  }
  if (x == 1 || x == 2) {
    return(TRUE)
  }
  for (all_number in 2:(x - 1)) {
    if (x %% all_number == 0) {
      return(FALSE)
    }
  }
  return(TRUE)
}

#' takes a positive integer x and returns the vector of prime factors of x
#'

get_factors <- function(x) {
  # returns a vector of prime factors of a positive integer x
  # Args:
  # x: positive integer
  # Return:
  # a vector, of prime factors of x
  if (as.integer(x) != x || x <= 0) {
    stop("x must be a positive integer.")
  }
  prime_list <- 1
  for (number in 2:x)
  {
    if (x %% number == 0 & is_prime(number)) {
      while (x %% number == 0) {
        x <- x / number
        prime_list <- c(prime_list, number)
      }
    }
  }
  prime_list
}

# Question 2-------------------------------

#' Returns true if x is a prime number, false otherwise
#'

is_prime <- function(x) {
  # returns whether a positive integer is prime
  # Args:
  # x: positive integer
  # Return:
  # a boolean, whether the statement is true
  if (as.integer(x) != x || x <= 0) {
    stop("x must be a positive integer.")
  }
  if (x == 1 || x == 2) {
    return(TRUE)
  }
  for (all_number in 2:(x - 1)) {
    if (x %% all_number == 0) {
      return(FALSE)
    }
  }
  return(TRUE)
}

#' takes a positive integer x and returns the vector of prime factors of x
#'

get_factors <- function(x) {
  # returns a vector of prime factors of a positive integer x
  # Args:
  # x: positive integer
  # Return:
  # a vector, of prime factors of x
  if (as.integer(x) != x || x <= 0) {
    stop("x must be a positive integer.")
  }
  prime_list <- 1
  for (number in 2:x)
  {
    if (x %% number == 0 & is_prime(number)) {
      while (x %% number == 0) {
        x <- x / number
        prime_list <- c(prime_list, number)
      }
    }
  }
  prime_list
}


x <- sample(x = 1e4, size = 1)
y <- get_factors(x)
this_works <- prod(y) == x & all(is_prime(y))
x <- sample(x = 9999, size = 1)
y <- get_factors(x)
this_works <- prod(y) == x & all(is_prime(y))
